21/10/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic announced Monday (20 October) that he has set 23 November as the official date of parliamentary elections.
In Croatia's embassies and consular missions abroad, the vote will take place a day earlier.
In his address to the public, Mesic urged all eligible voters to participate in the elections for the new parliament and government.
"With your votes you will directly influence the development of Croatia, thus determining your own future as well," he said.
The formal campaign season begins on 6 November and ends on 21 November.
The justice ministry says a total of 91 political parties have registered to nominate candidates so far.
(MediaScan - 21/10/03;
HINA, BBC - 20/10/03)
